# Implementation Plan - Table Status Indicators & Dashboard Segregation

This plan implements a unified status indication across all appointments tables in the project, introduces an appointment history view for patients, and separates the doctor's appointment requests from confirmed lists.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Unified Status Indicators in "Type" Columns

We will display a color-coded status indicator dot inside the **Type** column in every table displaying appointments.
- **Color Coding**:
  - `Pending` (Approval Pending): Yellow/Orange (`#f59e0b`)
  - `Confirmed` (Approved/Upcoming): Green (`#10b981`)
  - `Completed`: Purple/Indigo (`#8b5cf6` or `#06b6d4`)
  - `Cancelled` (Rejected): Red (`#ef4444`)
- **Impacted Tables**:
  - Patient Dashboard Upcoming Appointments list
  - Doctor Dashboard Daily Schedule queue list
  - Doctor appointments list (`DoctorAppointmentsComponent`)
  - Doctor appointment requests list (`DoctorRequestsComponent`)

---

### 2. Patient Dashboard Segmentation (Active vs. Historical)

We will introduce a new sidebar route for patients: **Appointment History** (`/patient/history`).
- **Sidebar Entry**:
  - Add **Appointment History** sidebar link in [sidebar.component.html](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/shared/components/sidebar/sidebar.component.html).
- **Routing**:
  - Add `/patient/history` child route in [app-routing.module.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/app-routing.module.ts) mapping to `DashboardComponent` with data `{ historyOnly: true }`.
- **Component Filtering**:
  - Read active route data in [dashboard.component.ts](file:///d:/shivam/doctor-appointment-system/doctor-appointment-frontend/src/app/features/dashboard/dashboard.component.ts) to toggle `historyMode`.
  - Filter `getFilteredAppointments()`:
    - **Dashboard**: Only show `Confirmed` & `Pending` appointments where the date has not passed yet.
    - **History**: Show all `Completed`, `Cancelled`, or past-date appointments.

